cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "mneme: Local-First AI Flashcard Generator with Interpretable Difficulty Scoring"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Debes
    given-names: Anwar
    affiliation: "University of Agder (UiA)"
abstract: >
  mneme converts any PDF, EPUB, Markdown, HTML, or plain-text source into a
  spaced-repetition flashcard deck using a local large language model
  (via Ollama). All processing runs on the user's machine: no cloud API,
  no data leakage, no per-card cost. Optional card-difficulty scoring
  uses a Tsetlin Machine to produce interpretable rules ("this card is
  hard because [clauses]"). Decks are written to Anki via the AnkiConnect
  plugin or exported as a portable .apkg file.
version: 0.2.0
date-released: 2026-06-12
license: MIT
keywords:
  - Anki
  - flashcards
  - spaced repetition
  - FSRS
  - local-first AI
  - Ollama
  - Tsetlin Machine
  - interpretable AI
  - education
